A KDF soldier who was killed in Kulbiyow attack in Somalia was buried on Saturday. Family, relatives and friends described Gideon Nyapindi as a hardworking and friendly individual. He was buried in Kesogon village, Trans Nzoia county. He last visited his home in December last year. In November last year, Nyapindi&rsquo;s mother Esther Chemeli was involved in a road accident and is now paralysed.Nyapindi was born in 1989 and has served as a KDF private since 2010. &ldquo;We have lost an energetic and dedicated young man, who was on a mission of enhancing peace,&rdquo; area MCA John Likovere said. He said the government should swiftly compensate the family. This was the third time the soldier had gone to Somalia.